article.headline: Rice 81, Navy 55
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Michael Harris scored 24 points and Brock Gillespie added 16, including four 3-pointers, to lead Rice to an 81-55 win over Navy Monday night. Harris also had five blocks and seven rebounds. Morris Almond had 13 points and two blocks and Jason McKrieth scored 10. Jeff Charles led Navy with 13 points. The game was tied at 14-14 in the first half before Rice (7-2) outscored Navy (2-7) 30-12, including a 14-0 run to take a 44-26 halftime lead. Rice shot 60 percent from the field in the second half and led by as many as 31 points. Both teams turned the ball over often. Navy finished with 26 turnovers and Rice had 23. Rice had 15 steals.
